column.description: This is the three character species code that includes species and hybrid information
This is the common name for the species, which includes hybrid descriptions.
This is the scientific name for the species, which includes hybrid descriptions.
This is a yes/no field that indicates whether or not the species is a primate.
This is the maximum blood that can be drawn per kg
This is the maximum percent of the animal's blood that can be drawn (expressed as a decimal, where 1 indicates 100%)
This is the number of days that must elapse to full reconstitute from a max blood draw
This is the two character species code that is used by the IACUC to group like species.
Determines which dataset the row belongs to (e.g. cycle_data, daily_observations)
The category to which the data belongs (e.g. cycle data includes 'tumescence_index', 'vaginal_bleeding', 'purple_color', etc.)
Animal account made up of three parts: project(xxx)-point(xx)-subpoint(xx)
